 JavaBot — AI-Powered FAQ Chatbot (Java)

A Java-based chatbot that combines **rule-based dialogue handling** with a
lightweight, dependency-free **NLP text-similarity engine** to answer
frequently asked questions in real time. Comes with both a **Swing GUI**
and a **CLI** front-end.

 ✨ Features

- **Natural Language Processing (from scratch, zero dependencies)**
  - Tokenization, stopword removal, light stemming
  - Cosine similarity over term-frequency vectors to match user input
    against the FAQ knowledge base
- **Hybrid logic**
  - Rule-based responses for greetings, thanks, goodbyes, name capture, time
  - Similarity-based matching for FAQ-style questions
  - Fallback responses that log unmatched questions to `data/unanswered.txt`
    for easy review and retraining
- **Trainable knowledge base** — add new Q&A pairs by editing
  `data/faqs.txt`, no recompilation needed
- **Two interfaces**
  - `ChatbotGUI` — a Swing desktop chat window for real-time interaction
  - `ChatbotCLI` — a console chat loop for quick testing / headless use

